The International Press Centre (IPC) has urged President Muhammadu Buhari to fulfill his 2019 election campaign promises. The Programme Manager of the centre, Sanmi Falobi, in a release detailing 30 of such promises in documentation done by IPC’s Media Monitoring Team, quoted the IPC Director, Mr. Lanre Arogundade, as saying that this was done in line with the tradition of IPC, which in 2011 documented 91 campaign promises of ex- President Goodluck Jonathan. He said such promises covered pledges on specific and general issues on road/rail infrastructure, education, agriculture, poverty eradication and inclusion of youths/women in government as well as fight against corruption and insecurity. Some of the promises included completing the Ibadan/Kano phase of the Lagos/Kano rail link;  the Port Harcourt/Maiduguri line;  the Itakpa/Warri link to Abuja through Lokoja; the Second Niger Bridge and the East West Road connecting Warri, Delta State, to Oron, Akwa Ibom State, through Kaiama and Port Harcourt in Bayelsa and Rivers states and to establish a “peoples moni bank.” South East rail: Amaechi has created problem for me — Buhari Eastern rail line: Amaechi has created problem for me, says Buhari 9 things Buhari promised Nigerians in 2018 Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin